    "Specifically, it focused on January 2023, comprising a random sample of 1,313 Tweets from a dataset of 1.3 million tweets.For the fine-tuning section of the three LLMs, we aim to allocate at least 15 % or more of the dataset to the evaluation set and the remaining 85 % to the training sets.We structure the training sets in increments of 50, 100, 250, 500, 1000, and 1500 samples, depending on the dataset's size.",
    "If the evaluation contains fewer than 100 rows or less than two instances of the minority class (the least frequent class), we adjust its proportion upwards until these conditions are fulfilled.",
    "Beyond meeting these prerequisites, the evaluation set proportion is incrementally expanded by 5 % as long as it does not compromise the planned training set sizes.",
    "This approach aims to optimize the evaluation sample size across an array of training set dimensions, thereby enabling a comprehensive assessment of how varying training data volumes impact the performance of all three LLMs.",
    "This approach also facilitates a comparative analysis using identical datasets for zero-shot learning, few-shot learning, and fine-tuning (Table 1)."
